      "settings": {
        "image": "shopify://shop_images/the-Christmas-Story-03.png",
        "image_mask": "none",
        "image2_mask": "none",
        "subtitle": "",
        "title": "",
        "text": "<p>So one night in the little town of Bethlehem, hidden away in a small stable, the Word became flesh. Contrary to some popular Christmas songs, the night Jesus was born would not have been a silent night. All would not have been calm, and all would not have been bright. It would be a night filled with the stench of animals, and the cries of birth pains as Mary delivered this promised rescuer onto a dirt floor now covered in blood. </p><p>No one would have chosen to have a child there. No one, except for God. </p><p></p>",
